   <div class='description_text'>
        His artworks offer many welcome surprises to the artist as he develops the ideas. Here, the same pieces that make up
        the 'bark' of the tree float on the surface much like logs in a river or cellulose fibers in a tree,
        expressing the reality that a branching system's function is often to convey material from a diffuse source
        to a concentrated destination, or vice versa.

   <br />
