    <div class='description_text'>
      
        <!--The artist is fascinated by the ubiquity of branching systems such as rivers, arteries, ancestry and evolution.
        The branched system is a basic organizational structure as fundamental to the universe as integers
        and platonic solids. -->
        
        Because he has often experienced 'Aha!' moments when working with materials, it is essential to his process
        that some elements of the artwork evolve during fabrication. One of the last details to emerge was the treatment
        of the trunk end. Here, as in the dissection of an organism, the further slicing of the tree results in new
        and perhaps surprising knowledge about its interior structure.
        
   </div>

